0said%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20have%20to%20pay%20attention%20to%20the%20fluctuating%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edollar-euro%20exchange%20rate%20and%20how%20his%20purchasing%20power%20might%20change%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d058b977-db9e-45c6-b3fb-b81bff9c7415%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEnlisting%20in%20the%20US%20Military%20and%20beginning%20a%20life%20in%20Germany%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlvarado%20comes%20from%20a%20military%20family%2C%20and%20his%20dad%20served%20in%20WWII.%20%26quot%3BMy%20father%20was%20there%20for%20D-Day%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20his%20family%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20Texas%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewas%20poor%2C%20and%20all%20of%20his%20brothers%20enlisted%20for%20better%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlvarado%20wasn't%20always%20set%20on%20Germany%2C%20and%20after%20the%20military%2C%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehe%20considered%20a%20career%20as%20a%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epolice%20officer%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20Washington%2C%20DC.%20He%20passed%20his%20exams%20but%20ultimately%20decided%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Germany%2C%20Alvarado%20took%20up%20jobs%20as%20a%20dishwasher%20and%20newspaper%20delivery%20driver.%20He%20said%20it%20was%20enough%20to%20support%20his%20family%2C%20and%20his%20economic%20prospects%20seemed%20better%20than%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20September%2011%2C%202001%2C%20terrorist%20attacks%2C%20Alvarado%20decided%20to%20enlist%20in%20the%20military%20reserves.%20He%20served%20for%20eight%20years%2C%20seeing%20two-and-a-half%20years%20of%20active%20duty%20in%20Afghanistan.%20He%20was%20injured%20there%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eofficially%20retired%20from%20service%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlvarado%20returned%20to%20Germany%2C%20where%20he%20worked%20as%20a%20cook%20and%20a%20driver%20for%20the%20US%20Military%20Postal%20Service.%20He%20also%20worked%20at%20an%20airport%2C%20where%20he%