call%20%E2%80%94%20ideally%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month%20%E2%80%94%20are%20thinking%20back%20to%20the%20Space%20Shuttle%20Columbia%20disaster.%20Because%20of%20damage%20to%20one%20of%20the%20vehicle's%20wings%2C%20that%20shuttle%20disintegrated%20as%20it%20reentered%20the%20atmosphere%20in%202003%2C%20killing%20all%20seven%20astronauts%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20NASA's%20been%20assessing%20its%20options%20for%20Williams%20and%20Wilmore%20for%20weeks%2C%20running%20tests%20with%20a%20Boeing%20thruster%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20and%20is%20now%20convening%20multiple%20boards%20and%20decision-making%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20time%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20fairly%20major%20discussion%2C%26quot%3B%20Ken%20Bowersox%2C%20the%20associate%20administrator%20of%20NASA's%20Space%20Operations%20Mission%20Directorate%2C%20said%20in%20a%20press%20briefing%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20this%20could%20be%20the%20agency's%20biggest%20safety%20decision%20in%20decades%20with%20two%20astronaut%20lives%20on%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b03978fc-da01-446a-9ff9-025634d4a4f1%5C%22%3EThe%20astronauts%20are%20at%20risk%20either%20way%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%20could%20send%20Williams%20and%20Wilmore%20back%20to%20Earth%20aboard%20Starliner%2C%20as%20they%20originally%20planned%20before%20the%20technical%20issues.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoeing%20has%20expressed%20full%20confidence%20in%20the%20vehicle%2C%20but%20some%20NASA%20officials%20still%20worry%20they%20don't%20have%20enough%20certainty%20about%20how%20the%20thrusters%20would%20behave%20when%20it%20comes%20time%20for%20the%20spaceship%20to%20push%20itself%20into%20a%20fall%20back%20to%20Earth.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22astronauts%20suni%20williams%20butch%20wilmore%20inside%20gadget-lined%20walls%20of%20international%20space%20station%20with%20a%20large%20American%20flag%20on%20the%20wa