%20financially%20right%20now.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOwning%20a%20home%20and%20having%20started%20a%20401(k)%20can%20create%20what's%20been%20called%20%26quot%3Bphantom%20wealth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThese%20millennials%20are%20rich%20on%20paper%20%E2%80%94%20but%20might%20not%20feel%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20two%20elder%20millennial%20friends%20sitting%20in%20a%20coffee%20shop%2C%20eating%20avocado%20toast%20(this%20is%20all%20about%20generational%20generalizations%2C%20so%20let's%20stick%20to%20the%20classics).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20monthly%20income%20is%20the%20same.%20They%20both%20spend%20the%20same%20on%20housing%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20grocery%20bills.%20They%20both%20feel%20the%20burden%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-kids-cost-raising-child-inflation-childcare-tax-exemptions-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20day%20care%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20their%20spending%20looks%20the%20same%20%E2%80%94%20that%20%2412%20toast%20hits%20the%20wallet%20just%20as%20hard%20for%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20imagine%20two%20big%20differences%3A%20One%20of%20the%20friends%20bought%20a%20home%20in%202019%3B%20the%20other%20still%20rents.%20The%20homeowner%20was%20automatically%20enrolled%20in%20her%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20her%20first%20job%20out%20of%20college%3B%20the%20other%20only%20started%20contributing%20to%20a%20401(k)%20more%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20these%20friends%20has%20millennial%20%26quot%3Bphantom%20wealth%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20wealth%20through%20homeownership%20and%20a%20401(k)%20that's%2C%20for%20the%20moment%2C%20only%20on%20paper.%20It%20doesn't%20always%20make%20them%20%3Cem%3Efeel%3C%2Fem%3E%20rich%20because%20they%20can't%20actually%20access%20the%20cash%20to%20spend%20it.%20But%20they're%20way%20ahead%20of%20their%20friend%20who%20still%20rents%20and%20started%20a%20retirement%20account%20later%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmillennials-personal-finance-real-estate-50742ffe%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%20reports%20that%20millennials%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20elder%20millennials%2C%20are%20doing%20surprisingly%20well%20financially%20after%20years%20of%20gloomy%20predictions%20about%20the%20generation.%20Compared%20to%20baby%20boomers%20when%20they%20were%20the%20same%20age%2C%20elder%20millennials%20are%20wealthier%2C%20it%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20big%20driver%20of%20this%20is%20what%20the%20Journal%20calls%20%26quot%3Bphantom%20wealth%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20illiquid%20wealth%20gained%20through%20real%20estate%20gains%20and%20rising%20retirement%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20similar%20conclusion%20to%20what%20my%20colleague%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investments-stocks-millennial-wealth-doubled-in-pandemic-economy-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Juliana%20Kaplan%20recently%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investments-stocks-millennial-wealth-doubled-in-pandemic-economy-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMillennials%20are%20doing%20just%20fine%20financially%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(Hold%20on%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0I'll%20get%20to%20the%20caveats%20in%20a%20second.)%20That's%20because%20of%20a%20mix%20of%20factors%20like%20student%20loan%20payment%20pauses%20and%20forgiveness%2C%20surging%20home%20prices%20across%20much%20of%20the%20country%2C%20and%20a%20stock%20market%20that's%20boomed%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20picture%20is%20not%20all%20bright%3A%20There%20is%20more%20drastic%20inequality%20among%20well-off%20millennials%20and%20those%20who%20are%20struggling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20wealth%20gap%20between%20the%20top%2020%25%20and%20bottom%2020%25%20of%20millennials%20is%20bigger%20than%20it%20was%20for%20boomers%20when%20they%20were%20a%20similar%20age%2C%20the%20Journal%20reported.%20Black%20millennials%20are%20half%20as%20likely%20to%20own%20a%20home%20as%20white%20millennials%20(a%20bigger%20gap%20than%20other%20generations).%20And%20because%20real%20estate%20is%20the%20biggest%20driver%20of%20millennial%20wealth%2C%20that%20has%20a%20huge%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20always%20been%20maddening%20for%20all%20involved%20to%20try%20to%20make%20sweeping%20generalizations%20about%20millennials%20(or%20any%20generation).%20And%20so%20many%20factors%20(medical%20costs%2C%20student%20debt%2C%20education%2C%20white%20collar%20vs.%20blue%20collar%20work%2C%20race%2C%20family%20wealth%2C%20geography%2C%20etc.)%20complicate%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20%26quot%3Bphantom%20wealth%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20form%20of%20illiquid%20real%20estate%20and%20retirement%20savings%20might%20be%20why%2C%20right%20now%2C%20it%20seems%20very%20surprising%20that%20millennials%20are%20doing%20%26quot%3Bbetter%26quot%3B%20than%20boomers%20did%20at%20this%20age.%20It%20sure%20doesn't%20always%20feel%20like%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20More%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmillennials-personal-finance-real-estate-50742ffe%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20dramatic%20turnaround%20in%20millennials'%20finances%3C%2Fa%3E%20(The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-wealth-house-rich-cash-poor-retirement-homeowner-budgeting-economy-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723674889000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bd201a5da406397bf6130a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%